s buffs will greatly vary.  I honestly do not know what buffs will be available as I am used to standing in a pile of people and getting hit with lvl 65 group spells.  Shammys/Clerics/Druids will know their buffing capabilities far more than I can predict so let them decide how buffs are done.  All tanks will need highest cleric buffs possible (or Po9/Symbol can sometimes give more), HoS/Focus, STA, and if possible Brells from a Pally.  Everyone else should be given as much hp as possible but with more efficient spells like Blessing of Aego rather than individual buffs.  Obviously all melee need haste as well as all casters needing crack.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry about wasting your time with that last paragraph that really didn't say anything useful but I honestly don't know what to say about buffs so we're moving on.  Once everything is ready to go an officer or a trusted person should me made a looter.  This is done through the raid utility by clicking &lt;&lt;gasp&gt;&gt; add looter I believe with someone selected.  The looter should be added because the raid leader is going to be so busy with everything else they shouldn't lose concentration to loot.  The looter should loot all droppable items and halt the raid on all important no drop items.  The best way I found is to make a chat channel for every item that is to be rolled on.  The looter will announce to the raid several times for everyone that needs the item to join the channel.  Once everyone is in the channel the looter should type /list &lt;channel #&gt; and do a /ran from 1 to the number of people in the channel (or # - 1 if the looter doesn't need).  For example in Kael a leather bracer drops:<br>
<br>
The looter should type something like:<br>
/rsay All in need of &lt;link of bracer&gt; please join MAbracer.<br>
<br>
Spam it a few times to make sure all druids, monks, and bsts that might need it see it.  Then type /list &lt;#&gt; and you should get something like:<br>
<br>
Channel MAbracer(4) members:<br>
*looter, Shabadoo, Bob, Whotfever<br>
<br>
where looter is the looters name.  The looter will then type /ran 1 4 (or /ran 1 3) and whatever number comes up that person gets the loot.  The list is always compiled based on the order people enter the channel so it will be the same for everyone.<br>
<br>
